1
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:58,892
Is something wrong?

2
00:00:58,975 --> 00:00:59,809
EPISODE 14

3
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:18,078
It's been a while.

4
00:01:25,543 --> 00:01:26,920
Thank you.

5
00:01:28,630 --> 00:01:30,673
Were you on your way somewhere yesterday?

6
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:32,801
Home. I stopped by the book store.

7
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:35,929
How was golf on Saturday?

8
00:01:36,012 --> 00:01:37,013
Good.

9
00:01:37,972 --> 00:01:40,517
What you said that day
wasn't a joke, was it?

10
00:01:41,976 --> 00:01:43,978
-Of course not.
-I was a bit surprised.

11
00:01:46,731 --> 00:01:49,859
If you're not busy,
can you buy me a latte?

12
00:01:51,402 --> 00:01:52,695
Do you know CafÃ© Deung?

13
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:12,132
Coffee always tastes good.

14
00:02:12,882 --> 00:02:14,050
No wonder it's addictive.

15
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:17,512
We can't help but have them
in our line of work.

16
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:19,973
Why do you think I got a divorce?

17
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:23,268
As if you'd actually answer.

18
00:02:23,351 --> 00:02:26,062
They all say it's because
they have nothing in common.

19
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:28,106
That's only true for celebrities.

20
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:31,151
My husband dumped me.

21
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:36,447
He fell for another woman,
so what else could it be?

22
00:02:36,531 --> 00:02:38,241
Did he ask for the divorce?

23
00:02:38,324 --> 00:02:42,245
No. He wanted me to forgive him
and move on,

24
00:02:43,204 --> 00:02:44,831
but I couldn't.

25
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:46,749
Should I have?

26
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:49,627
Time will only tell
if you've made the right choice.

27
00:02:50,336 --> 00:02:52,839
Taking action can sometimes
give you the best result

28
00:02:52,922 --> 00:02:54,716
while sometimes it doesn't.

29
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:02,348
You seemed all right that day.

30
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:06,436
At the golf club, I mean.

31
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:08,980
It was nice to see you be open about it.

32
00:03:09,063 --> 00:03:12,442
I'm probably at ease
since I didn't cause the divorce.

33
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:17,196
Being the victim
could lead to more anger at times.

34
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:20,867
-It wasn't easy.
-Of course it's not.

35
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:25,121
Why are men like that?

36
00:03:25,204 --> 00:03:28,833
Why can't they be loyal
and keep their promises?

37
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:29,959
Is that so hard to do?

38
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:31,461
I wouldn't know.

39
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:34,923
I don't understand people
who break their promises.

40
00:03:35,006 --> 00:03:38,009
What about your friends?
The ones who are married.

41
00:03:38,092 --> 00:03:39,427
About a third are divorced.

42
00:03:39,510 --> 00:03:41,721
-For what reason?
-Personality differences.

43
00:03:41,804 --> 00:03:43,556
I should hear both sides of the story,

44
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:47,560
but some say they had no chance
because their wives weren't up to par.

45
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:48,686
There are many reasons,

46
00:03:49,437 --> 00:03:51,689
just like how there's a reason
behind every death.

47
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,107
Has anyone switched partners?

48
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:55,401
-Two.
-How are they?

49
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:57,237
One of them is living a good life

50
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,822
while another had to try four times.

51
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:02,867
-He married four times?
-Yes.

52
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:04,911
How can someone marry four times?

53
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,454
Once is stressful enough.

54
00:04:06,537 --> 00:04:10,250
From what I can tell,
only the first divorce is the hardest.

55
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,210
Do you envy them as a man yourself?

56
00:04:12,293 --> 00:04:14,003
Of course not.

57
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:18,258
Life should be simple
especially in this hectic world.

58
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:25,098
How's Ji-a?

59
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:27,225
Goodness. Do you remember her name?

60
00:04:27,308 --> 00:04:29,644
It's not like I have dementia.
Of course I remember.

61
00:04:30,728 --> 00:04:32,313
She's in my care, of course.

62
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:35,984
I was sitting on the fence because of her.

63
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:39,946
You wouldn't know
since you're not married,

64
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:43,616
but trust is the most important thing
between a married couple.

65
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:46,119
It is for any relationship.

66
00:04:47,161 --> 00:04:48,871
Where will you go from here then?

67
00:04:50,248 --> 00:04:52,500
-Forget I asked.
-Are you headed home then?

68
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:53,710
Yes.

69
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:56,546
Do you cook for yourself?

70
00:04:56,629 --> 00:04:57,797
Only on rare occasions.

71
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,966
I order in or eat at
a restaurant near home.

72
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:02,468
You eat just about anything
apart from caviar.

73
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:04,929
That's right.
So how did you send your mother off?

74
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:08,349
-My mom?
-Was there a burial?

75
00:05:09,517 --> 00:05:12,228
Yes, she was laid to rest
beside my father.

76
00:05:14,772 --> 00:05:15,815
What about you?

77
00:05:15,898 --> 00:05:17,608
Do you know what I regret the most?

78
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:21,696
My mother wanted
to have her ashes scattered in the water,

79
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:23,656
so that's what I did.

80
00:05:24,866 --> 00:05:26,034
I regret it though.

81
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:29,370
Cremating her
or scattering her ashes in water?

82
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:30,496
Both.

83
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:34,792
I should have buried her ashes
below a tree or kept it someplace.

84
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,755
Did your mother appear in your dream?

85
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:41,424
-No.
-Then she's resting in peace.

86
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:46,137
My mom visited me in my dream many times
and said she was cold.

87
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:49,599
Goodness.

88
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:52,185
But her ashes are already gone.

89
00:05:52,268 --> 00:05:53,394
Oh, dear.

90
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,482
-What about memorial services?
-I hold a small one every year.

91
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:04,155
Parents are meant to sacrifice
and children are born to regret.

92
00:06:05,698 --> 00:06:07,241
And I do a lot of that.

93
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:09,327
I'm no better.

94
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:10,870
You seem like a good daughter.

95
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:13,247
Most daughters are good to their mothers.

96
00:06:13,331 --> 00:06:16,125
I know, but it's a long story though.

97
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:18,461
Us brats should
grab a drink sometime then.

98
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:20,755
Sure.

99
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:23,257
MADAM HONG

100
00:06:25,093 --> 00:06:26,260
MADAM HONG

101
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:27,303
I should take this.

102
00:06:28,513 --> 00:06:29,597
Sure.

103
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:34,727
Where the hell were you all day?

104
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:35,853
I had a meeting.

105
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:36,979
All day?

106
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:39,023
I also worked out.

107
00:06:40,024 --> 00:06:42,360
Mother, put up your hands like this.

108
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:45,113
Come on.

109
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,914
You've got to be kidding me.

110
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,416
Are you playing games with me?

111
00:06:58,543 --> 00:07:00,461
You should try boxing too.

112
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:01,629
It's a great exercise.

113
00:07:01,712 --> 00:07:02,713
Save it for yourself.

114
00:07:03,297 --> 00:07:05,216
Mop the floors and then help with dinner.

115
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:06,300
Sure.

116
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:11,931
Isn't the housekeeper here?

117
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:17,019
-I hear you hire help.
-Money doesn't grow on trees.

118
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:19,689
Why do we need one
when there are two women in the house?

119
00:07:20,231 --> 00:07:22,400
Of course. You're absolutely right.

120
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:28,739
Is she an idiot?

121
00:07:32,368 --> 00:07:34,495
Sa Pi-young, you foolish girl.

122
00:07:34,579 --> 00:07:36,581
You let some idiot replace you.

123
00:07:41,586 --> 00:07:43,963
-Maybe she's not home.
-Didn't you call her?

124
00:07:44,046 --> 00:07:45,756
I had no time for that today.

125
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:49,427
She might be washing. Call her.

126
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:52,388
Don't you know the combination?

127
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:53,556
Hello?

128
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:55,099
Aren't you home?

129
00:07:55,183 --> 00:07:58,102
I'm out to buy some twisted doughnuts.

130
00:07:58,186 --> 00:07:59,187
Twisted doughnuts?

131
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:03,941
Yes, I had a sudden craving.

132
00:08:04,525 --> 00:08:06,235
Where are you? Someplace far?

133
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:09,155
I'm behind Gangnam Sauna on foot.

134
00:08:09,238 --> 00:08:10,364
I'll be right there.

135
00:08:10,948 --> 00:08:12,116
You'll come to me?

136
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:14,577
Are you at my place?

137
00:08:17,121 --> 00:08:20,541
You crave everything and anything
when you're pregnant.

138
00:08:21,209 --> 00:08:23,377
I remember you craving pheasant dumplings

139
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,796
when you had Sa-hyeon.

140
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:28,382
That was with our eldest, not him.

141
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:29,967
Was it our eldest?

142
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:34,555
Anyway, we couldn't kill
since it'd be bad luck,

143
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:37,475
so I went through hoops
to buy pheasant meat.

144
00:08:37,558 --> 00:08:39,435
I can't believe you remember all that.

145
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:44,774
Are you upset? What's with the long face?

146
00:08:46,817 --> 00:08:51,197
Just imagine all the cravings she
would have had. I wasn't there for her.

147
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:53,241
I told her to call us anytime.

148
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:55,326
If only we had lived closer by.

149
00:08:55,409 --> 00:08:57,537
Even today, she went out
to get some herself.

150
00:08:58,412 --> 00:09:00,831
You have the last month to make up for it.

151
00:09:00,915 --> 00:09:04,418
Of course. It's your heart that matters.

152
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:07,463
There's a big difference
between helping reluctantly

153
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:09,590
and doing so because you want to.

154
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:14,637
What was that word again?
It starts with a Q.

155
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,721
Right.

156
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:17,473
Quality is what matters.

157
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:27,692
Don't scoop the rice. It'll get cold.

158
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:29,735
We should have dinner.

159
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:33,823
Don't you have any common courtesy?
The head of the household isn't home.

160
00:09:36,325 --> 00:09:37,535
Yu-sin will be late.

161
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:39,495
-He's running late?
-Yes.

162
00:09:39,579 --> 00:09:41,414
Why didn't you tell me though?

163
00:09:41,497 --> 00:09:43,708
Team dinners aren't important enough
to mention.

164
00:09:44,792 --> 00:09:46,586
Then I wouldn't have made all this.

165
00:09:47,503 --> 00:09:50,673
You and I need to eat though.
Should we starve instead?

166
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:52,800
As Ji-a says, you're super annoying.

167
00:09:52,883 --> 00:09:54,468
Why go to these lengths then?

168
00:09:54,552 --> 00:09:58,431
My grandma said that
eating well gives you a glow.

169
00:09:58,514 --> 00:10:00,182
Who the hell do you think you are?

170
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:03,060
-Me?
-You keep talking backâ¦

171
00:10:03,769 --> 00:10:06,897
How could you not tell me
when you saw me making all this food?

172
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,358
I thought you knew.

173
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,486
SHOULD I JUST SLAM HER TO THE FLOOR

174
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:15,156
AND FLATTEN HER LIKE A GUTTED SQUID?

175
00:10:15,239 --> 00:10:16,574
You eat this much, right?

176
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:24,248
Get in!

177
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:26,876
Father, the shop's right over there.

178
00:10:28,544 --> 00:10:31,297
-Welcome.
-Gosh, it smells incredible.

179
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:34,800
This is unbelievable.

180
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:36,469
Do you like snacks like these?

181
00:10:36,552 --> 00:10:38,179
I'm just like everyone else.

182
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:43,184
Those are twisted doughnuts
and those are spicy corn dogs.

183
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:45,227
Honey, it's the doughnuts you love.

184
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:47,438
Do you like doughnuts, Mother?

185
00:10:47,521 --> 00:10:48,814
Those with red beans inside.

186
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:53,069
The cheese doughnuts are good too.

187
00:10:53,152 --> 00:10:55,529
-We'll take a few of everything.
-Sure.

188
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:58,074
They use glutinous rice.

189
00:10:58,157 --> 00:10:59,450
-Glutinous rice?
-Yes.

190
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:00,743
Go ahead and eat one.

191
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:10,628
Just watching you has our mouth-watering.

192
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:12,338
Is it good?

193
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:17,510
-I feel so much better.
-Is there a decent restaurant nearby?

194
00:11:17,593 --> 00:11:19,345
We should have them while they're hot.

195
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:20,805
Here you go.

196
00:11:21,889 --> 00:11:23,057
Thank you.

197
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:28,604
We'll order bossam and three bowls of
makguksu. Make one of them spicy.

198
00:11:28,687 --> 00:11:29,522
We'll share.

199
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:33,150
-Right away.
-Let's see.

200
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:39,532
We'll have the noodles when they get here.

201
00:11:39,615 --> 00:11:41,492
We didn't even have a proper lunch today.

202
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:43,828
-Goodness.
-We had the final payment to make.

203
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:47,998
Hye-ryung's moving the day after tomorrow
and they've filed their papers.

204
00:11:52,586 --> 00:11:53,546
This is really good.

205
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:55,589
This too.

206
00:11:56,966 --> 00:11:57,925
How about another?

207
00:11:58,008 --> 00:11:59,468
I'll have it for dessert.

208
00:12:08,894 --> 00:12:10,187
Isn't it good?

209
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:13,190
This isn't like the twisted doughnuts
I've had before.

210
00:12:27,371 --> 00:12:29,331
Mother, your galbijjim is the best

211
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:30,499
as are the other food.

212
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:34,670
Did I cook for hours
just to feed this bitch?

213
00:12:34,753 --> 00:12:36,755
Some enjoy food made by others

214
00:12:36,839 --> 00:12:39,133
while some like to cook themselves.

215
00:12:39,216 --> 00:12:41,302
I guess you'd rather
have others cook for you.

216
00:12:41,385 --> 00:12:43,137
Just eat quietly.

217
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:44,263
Sure.

218
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:47,516
I get so hungry after a workout.

219
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:54,398
Are you finished already?

220
00:12:57,234 --> 00:12:59,236
Are you perhaps feeling under the weather?

221
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:06,911
I feel much better
now that my stomach's full.

222
00:13:08,537 --> 00:13:09,663
You should stay with us.

223
00:13:10,247 --> 00:13:11,207
For what?

224
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:13,834
What do you mean?
It's better than her being alone.

225
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:17,004
We have a yard big enough for walks,
so you won't have to go out.

226
00:13:17,087 --> 00:13:19,924
I can look after you,
and we've already told his brother.

227
00:13:20,007 --> 00:13:22,676
She should move into my house
since it's safe there.

228
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:25,930
-And our house is a hazard?
-Her due date could be pushed up

229
00:13:26,013 --> 00:13:27,598
and her ob-gyn is close by.

230
00:13:27,681 --> 00:13:28,849
I guess he's right.

231
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:30,893
Why don't you two stay at my place?

232
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:33,521
-You should.
-You want us to live together?

233
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:34,939
There are three rooms.

234
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:39,068
It'll take a month
for the papers to be finalized.

235
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:41,695
We can have the wedding later,

236
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:44,198
but I want her to have the baby
while we're around.

237
00:13:44,281 --> 00:13:46,116
Of course. That's how it should be.

238
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,955
Shouldn't you at least
take a photo to celebrate?

239
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:52,748
Of course they should.

240
00:13:52,831 --> 00:13:56,085
At the thought of you

241
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:59,380
I toss and turn in my sleep

242
00:13:59,463 --> 00:14:02,716
A smile spreads over my face
at the thought of you

243
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:06,053
And that gets me through the day

244
00:14:06,136 --> 00:14:09,348
At the thought of you

245
00:14:09,848 --> 00:14:13,018
I only await this day

246
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:14,562
There was something

247
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:20,442
I wanted to say in your presence

248
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:26,198
So I held back and endured the wait

249
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:31,120
Everyone in this world

250
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:36,792
May call me a fool

251
00:14:39,336 --> 00:14:41,422
But it's all right

252
00:14:42,172 --> 00:14:45,634
Because

253
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:51,849
I love

254
00:14:51,932 --> 00:14:58,939
You

255
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:14,538
-Hey, Madam Hong.
-What time do you get off work?

256
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:15,706
I already am.

257
00:15:15,789 --> 00:15:18,125
-Han-seung wants to meet up.
-I have plans.

258
00:15:18,208 --> 00:15:19,960
With whom? I doubt it's a woman.

259
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,712
Why not?

260
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:23,881
I'll eat my hat if that's true.

261
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:26,634
Put it in writing
that you'll eat your hat.

262
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:27,801
Got it.

263
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:31,764
Hello?

264
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:36,685
Where are you?
I'll feed you the hat myself.

265
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:38,938
Who was that?

266
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:40,564
Don't change the subject.

267
00:15:40,648 --> 00:15:44,068
Bring her with you.
Drinks will definitely be on me today.

268
00:15:44,151 --> 00:15:46,528
-I'll call you back later then.
-Bring her!

269
00:15:49,114 --> 00:15:49,990
Why Madam Hong?

270
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:52,409
His name is Do-dam
and he's extremely talkative.

271
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:54,370
It's been his nickname since high school.

272
00:15:56,956 --> 00:16:00,042
-You should get going then.
-They gather to drink and talk nonsense.

273
00:16:13,222 --> 00:16:14,556
It's been a while.

274
00:16:16,517 --> 00:16:17,434
He's a fan.

275
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:23,357
This is Professor Park Hae-ryun,
my fiancÃ©.

276
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,733
I see.

277
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:30,239
It's your last week, isn't it?

278
00:16:30,739 --> 00:16:32,282
Yes.

279
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:35,911
-You did great.
-Thank you.

280
00:16:37,913 --> 00:16:38,956
Goodbye.

281
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:21,832
Let me know in advance
if you're eating out for dinner.

282
00:17:22,916 --> 00:17:25,044
Sending a message is not difficult.

283
00:17:25,961 --> 00:17:27,337
But I did.

284
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:28,839
I mean, to me.

285
00:17:29,506 --> 00:17:31,425
I cooked all sorts of dishes

286
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:34,178
only to hear you were eating out.

287
00:17:40,267 --> 00:17:42,019
Mother, you should put this on.

288
00:17:42,102 --> 00:17:44,730
It's for your eyes and mouth.
Your neck too.

289
00:17:46,356 --> 00:17:47,733
Should I do it for you?

290
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:55,157
You don't have deep wrinkles,
but the shallow ones must bother you.

291
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,950
It's common at your age though.

292
00:17:59,119 --> 00:18:00,120
How dare you!

293
00:18:01,455 --> 00:18:03,207
I just wanted to help you look young.

294
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,255
This is a great product.

295
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:24,520
How dare she call me old
in front of Yu-sin.

296
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,702
Should we pack the dishes
in that cupboard too?

297
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:41,745
Yes, please.

298
00:18:43,163 --> 00:18:45,165
You can pack all of those too.

299
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,168
-Please have this while you work.
-Thanks.

300
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:00,889
DONG-MA

301
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:18,240
-Hello?
-It's me.

302
00:19:19,616 --> 00:19:21,160
I'm at your apartment complex.

303
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:24,997
-Can't you come out?
-I'm outside.

304
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:27,124
You sound like you just woke up

305
00:19:27,749 --> 00:19:30,377
and your car's here.
Should I come to you instead?

306
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:33,547
-What's this about?
-I want to talk.

307
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:37,050
I'll be at Sagye.

308
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:45,559
-One Americano, please.
-Sure.

309
00:19:47,769 --> 00:19:49,438
It's not like you to order coffee.

310
00:19:55,611 --> 00:19:56,862
You know, right?

311
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:59,156
That's the style I like.

312
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:03,577
Messy hair and clothes
you can fall asleep in.

313
00:20:06,830 --> 00:20:07,706
What's going on?

314
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:10,918
How are your parents?

315
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:16,298
I dropped by because
you seemed upset the other day

316
00:20:17,090 --> 00:20:19,009
and to say I enjoyed your performance.

317
00:20:20,969 --> 00:20:23,555
-You always deliver.
-They passed away.

318
00:20:26,266 --> 00:20:27,142
Both of them.

319
00:20:28,018 --> 00:20:29,144
When?

320
00:20:33,523 --> 00:20:34,775
Was it yesterday?

321
00:20:40,697 --> 00:20:44,159
But I can't fly out to their funeral

322
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:46,245
because I'm the sole lead of the show.

323
00:21:13,146 --> 00:21:14,481
My dadâ¦

324
00:21:16,108 --> 00:21:18,318
fell down while playing tennis

325
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:20,070
and fractured his collarbone.

326
00:21:21,238 --> 00:21:23,115
That's why I pushed back the wedding.

327
00:21:24,408 --> 00:21:26,576
My mom was driving him back
from the hospital

328
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:30,872
after taking off his cast whenâ¦

329
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:36,586
Your dad's younger brother
lives close by, right?

330
00:21:46,221 --> 00:21:48,515
I'll send an employee
from our branch in Germany.

331
00:21:49,099 --> 00:21:51,601
-I still can't believe it.
-When did you last see them?

332
00:21:52,769 --> 00:21:54,062
Last fall.

333
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:04,573
You can't fall apart.

334
00:22:06,283 --> 00:22:07,117
Stay strong.

335
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:16,460
How did you still manage
to perform last night?

336
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,300
Your parentsâ¦

337
00:22:26,261 --> 00:22:27,846
were probably there to see you.

338
00:22:31,975 --> 00:22:33,060
I'm sure they were.

339
00:22:35,228 --> 00:22:38,565
Bada. Live a long, healthy life, okay?

340
00:22:42,110 --> 00:22:44,321
Hye-ryung wants to buy us dinner tomorrow.

341
00:22:45,530 --> 00:22:46,823
But I was going to do that.

342
00:22:46,907 --> 00:22:49,576
It doesn't matter who does.
We should still have one last meal.

343
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,828
She has a new name now. It's Bada.

344
00:22:51,912 --> 00:22:53,872
What for? It's not like she knows.

345
00:22:53,955 --> 00:22:55,874
She's a smart one,
so she'll catch on soon.

346
00:22:57,626 --> 00:22:59,086
Dogs take after their owners.

347
00:23:00,337 --> 00:23:01,880
Isn't that right, Bada?

348
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:04,257
There you go.

349
00:23:07,761 --> 00:23:10,806
How's the house? Is it in a pleasant spot?

350
00:23:11,765 --> 00:23:13,391
Yes, I slept well.

351
00:23:13,475 --> 00:23:16,561
That was probably because
you were exhausted.

352
00:23:18,105 --> 00:23:21,316
I can't believe things happened so fast.

353
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:22,984
We used to be family after allâ¦

354
00:23:23,068 --> 00:23:24,569
Tell me about it.

355
00:23:25,195 --> 00:23:28,657
I was truly happy
on my wedding day, you know.

356
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:30,200
We're sorry about what happened.

357
00:23:32,035 --> 00:23:35,372
Catholicism teaches us that we
have no one to blame but ourselves.

358
00:23:35,997 --> 00:23:38,208
I will just accept things as they are.

359
00:23:38,291 --> 00:23:41,670
You must have been an angel
in your past life,

360
00:23:42,420 --> 00:23:44,589
which is why you were born so beautiful.

361
00:23:44,673 --> 00:23:48,135
That must mean you were an angel too.

362
00:23:48,802 --> 00:23:50,220
Sa-hyeon as well.

363
00:23:50,971 --> 00:23:52,681
I guess only I was a menace.

364
00:23:53,431 --> 00:23:56,852
That's ridiculous.
You're nothing but masculine.

365
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:58,103
-An alpha male.
-Exactly.

366
00:23:58,186 --> 00:23:59,646
An alpha male?

367
00:24:00,897 --> 00:24:04,651
Anyway, I'm relieved that we can part ways

368
00:24:04,734 --> 00:24:06,570
with smiles on our faces.

369
00:24:06,653 --> 00:24:08,363
Are you never going to see me again?

370
00:24:08,446 --> 00:24:11,491
That's not what I meant.
We're technically not a family anymore.

371
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:13,410
Once a family, always a family.

372
00:24:13,493 --> 00:24:14,452
Of course.

373
00:24:15,537 --> 00:24:18,290
That's why I asked him
to let me see the baby once it's born.

374
00:24:19,791 --> 00:24:21,960
Right. You should stay friends.

375
00:24:22,043 --> 00:24:25,839
In foreign TV shows,
you see divorced couples stay friends.

376
00:24:25,922 --> 00:24:27,382
With no hard feelings.

377
00:24:27,465 --> 00:24:29,759
Sa-hyeon, let's do that.

378
00:24:32,679 --> 00:24:36,141
Although I don't regret it,
I've given it some thought.

379
00:24:36,224 --> 00:24:39,269
Maybe I should have had a baby
right after the marriage.

380
00:24:39,352 --> 00:24:41,104
That would have been nice.

381
00:24:41,188 --> 00:24:42,522
That was foolish of me.

382
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:45,525
You had a different view of life.
You can't call yourself a fool.

383
00:24:45,609 --> 00:24:48,653
Anyway, I'm grateful for the generosity
you showed me.

384
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:51,740
I should've cooked a meal for you myself.

385
00:24:51,823 --> 00:24:54,868
Nonsense. All that matters
is that we've had this gathering.

386
00:24:54,951 --> 00:24:55,994
Of course.

387
00:24:56,077 --> 00:24:58,830
Can I still visit you in Daejeon
from time to time

388
00:24:58,914 --> 00:25:02,626
as if you were my Mom and Dad,
and not in-laws?

389
00:25:02,709 --> 00:25:05,503
Of course. Come by
whenever you go golfing.

390
00:25:05,587 --> 00:25:07,339
And tell me what you'd like to eat.

391
00:25:07,422 --> 00:25:09,090
Yes, Mother.

392
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:14,387
That's great. Congratulations.

393
00:25:14,471 --> 00:25:15,722
You too.

394
00:25:16,223 --> 00:25:18,183
The wedding will happen in no time.

395
00:25:18,266 --> 00:25:19,100
Yes.

396
00:25:21,728 --> 00:25:23,230
What about Ga-bin though?

397
00:25:23,813 --> 00:25:25,690
I can't think of anything to say.

398
00:25:25,774 --> 00:25:27,150
Same here.

399
00:25:28,526 --> 00:25:31,071
Why don't we just go
to her final performance?

400
00:25:31,154 --> 00:25:34,324
I have a meeting
with the publishing agency that day.

401
00:25:34,908 --> 00:25:35,992
Thank you for dinner.

402
00:25:36,826 --> 00:25:38,912
Don't mention it.
Have a safe trip to Daejeon.

403
00:25:38,995 --> 00:25:39,871
Sure.

404
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:43,792
Mother, I'll text you from time to time.

405
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:45,418
Sure thing.

406
00:26:14,698 --> 00:26:15,573
Thank you.

407
00:26:28,837 --> 00:26:30,213
Have a good life.

408
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,091
You too.

409
00:27:06,624 --> 00:27:09,336
They say you need to spend time
with people to know them.

410
00:27:09,419 --> 00:27:10,670
Hye-ryung's proof of that.

411
00:27:10,754 --> 00:27:11,880
Tell me about it.

412
00:27:12,797 --> 00:27:14,883
She ended it all with a smile on her face.

413
00:27:14,966 --> 00:27:16,634
She was an angel in disguise.

414
00:27:16,718 --> 00:27:18,970
This is why people should be generous.

415
00:27:19,846 --> 00:27:23,475
Because you did everything she asked for,

416
00:27:23,558 --> 00:27:24,976
things ended amicably.

417
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:26,811
I hope she finds someone nice.

418
00:27:26,895 --> 00:27:29,856
Of course she will.
She's still quite young.

419
00:27:30,482 --> 00:27:32,359
Although, people will gossip for a while.

420
00:27:32,942 --> 00:27:35,528
What will she say when people
ask her about the divorce?

421
00:27:35,612 --> 00:27:37,864
What celebrities always say.

422
00:27:37,947 --> 00:27:39,824
"We had nothing in common,

423
00:27:40,658 --> 00:27:42,869
but we've decided to stay as friends."

424
00:27:56,424 --> 00:27:58,718
-Hello?
-Mr. Seo.

425
00:27:58,802 --> 00:28:00,512
Are you already home?

426
00:28:00,595 --> 00:28:02,263
Yes, I just got back.

427
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:06,643
-What's this about?
-How about a cocktail?

428
00:28:06,726 --> 00:28:08,061
I'm buying.

429
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:15,860
Where did you get this money?

430
00:28:18,780 --> 00:28:19,906
Mom.

431
00:28:20,949 --> 00:28:22,784
-Yes?
-We need to talk.

432
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:28,415
It's from Dad.

433
00:28:29,874 --> 00:28:31,584
Did you see him without telling us?

434
00:28:31,668 --> 00:28:32,919
Three times.

435
00:28:35,088 --> 00:28:38,299
-What did he say?
-He misses me and wants to know

436
00:28:38,383 --> 00:28:39,384
how I'm doing.

437
00:28:39,467 --> 00:28:42,804
-Did he tell you to keep it a secret?
-I just thought that I should.

438
00:28:42,887 --> 00:28:44,305
When did you last see him?

439
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:45,807
About a month ago.

440
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:48,226
Are you a saint or just stupid?

441
00:28:48,309 --> 00:28:49,936
He's still our dad.

442
00:28:50,019 --> 00:28:52,480
And we're his children.

443
00:28:52,564 --> 00:28:54,649
And look what he did to us.

444
00:29:39,986 --> 00:29:41,654
The bartender's cool, isn't she?

445
00:29:57,045 --> 00:29:58,671
You should try a sip of this too.

446
00:29:58,755 --> 00:30:00,340
-It's good.
-Isn't it sweet?

447
00:30:00,423 --> 00:30:02,300
-Only a little.
-Then I'll pass.

448
00:30:02,383 --> 00:30:04,844
I'd like to be comforted
with a touch of sweetness today.

449
00:30:06,137 --> 00:30:07,472
I moved out, you see.

450
00:30:10,642 --> 00:30:13,937
What did you think
of my husband when you saw him?

451
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:17,148
He was charming.

452
00:30:17,232 --> 00:30:20,610
A woman was drawn to him
because of that charm

453
00:30:20,693 --> 00:30:22,320
and she got knocked up on purpose.

454
00:30:23,947 --> 00:30:26,533
My husband fell for her antics
and requested a divorce.

455
00:30:28,034 --> 00:30:28,910
I agreed.

456
00:30:38,253 --> 00:30:40,004
What do you think of that?

457
00:30:42,006 --> 00:30:43,383
It's nonsensical.

458
00:30:43,466 --> 00:30:45,134
That's what I thought too.

459
00:30:46,427 --> 00:30:49,806
It's not my place to ask,
but does he really love this woman?

460
00:30:50,598 --> 00:30:52,225
Or is it because of the baby?

461
00:30:54,811 --> 00:30:56,729
Both, I guess.

462
00:30:58,022 --> 00:31:00,483
My pride is wounded

463
00:31:00,567 --> 00:31:02,151
and it hurts, honestly speaking.

464
00:31:02,235 --> 00:31:04,362
You should meet someone better.

465
00:31:04,445 --> 00:31:05,572
That'll heal your heart.

466
00:31:06,948 --> 00:31:10,285
AND THAT SOMEONE IS YOU

467
00:31:11,119 --> 00:31:14,455
I don't know. I've lost confidence now.

468
00:31:14,539 --> 00:31:17,292
In yourself?
Or have you lost trust in men?

469
00:31:17,959 --> 00:31:19,544
I've lost confidence in myself.

470
00:31:19,627 --> 00:31:22,171
We all have
our ups and downs in life, right?

471
00:31:22,255 --> 00:31:23,840
Things might get better for you.

472
00:31:23,923 --> 00:31:25,550
Like the actress Oh Yu-rim.

473
00:31:26,217 --> 00:31:29,387
Marrying the eldest son
of SF Electronics' CEO

474
00:31:29,470 --> 00:31:31,514
would be the most thrilling payback.

475
00:31:31,598 --> 00:31:34,642
This could just be temporary.
He might come back to you.

476
00:31:35,351 --> 00:31:38,229
-But there's a baby now.
-Kids don't keep people from divorcing.

477
00:31:38,313 --> 00:31:41,941
My father divorced my mother
after they had me too.

478
00:31:46,446 --> 00:31:48,323
How old were you?

479
00:31:49,157 --> 00:31:50,241
I was in my teens.

480
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:53,494
It must have been tough for you.

481
00:31:53,578 --> 00:31:54,537
Was it amicable?

482
00:31:54,621 --> 00:31:57,206
I said goodbye with a smile on my face.

483
00:31:57,707 --> 00:32:01,127
There's no need to end a chapter with
a frown. Easier said than done though.

484
00:32:12,472 --> 00:32:14,974
-You have a suitcase, right?
-Yes.

485
00:32:15,058 --> 00:32:17,310
That should be reserved for valuables.

486
00:32:17,393 --> 00:32:18,269
But it's nighttime.

487
00:32:18,353 --> 00:32:20,313
You don't want to leave anything out

488
00:32:20,396 --> 00:32:22,815
and things will be hectic tomorrow.
Just say the word.

489
00:32:22,899 --> 00:32:26,027
You're wearing yourself out.
It was already a moving day for you.

490
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:27,904
-I didn't do any work.
-You should rest at night.

491
00:32:27,987 --> 00:32:29,113
It won't wear me out.

492
00:32:29,197 --> 00:32:31,449
You're overestimating yourself.
Take it back.

493
00:32:32,533 --> 00:32:33,785
There.

494
00:32:40,458 --> 00:32:42,710
Maybe you were right not to get married.

495
00:32:44,921 --> 00:32:46,172
Do you regret it?

496
00:32:46,923 --> 00:32:50,009
No. In a few years, you might
be glad that you had that divorce.

497
00:32:50,843 --> 00:32:52,095
Right.

498
00:32:52,178 --> 00:32:55,306
I'm not going to regret
my marriage or my divorce though.

499
00:32:56,140 --> 00:32:58,518
They're all valuable life lessons.

500
00:32:59,143 --> 00:33:02,146
Any experience that you have in life
can be put to good use.

501
00:33:02,230 --> 00:33:04,565
How long does it take
for divorces to be finalized?

502
00:33:06,943 --> 00:33:08,236
A month if there's no child.

503
00:33:08,319 --> 00:33:10,947
Once it's over,
reporters will get wind of it.

504
00:33:13,700 --> 00:33:17,620
I know you're close to Ms. Sa
and Ms. Lee, but I'm also your teammate.

505
00:33:18,329 --> 00:33:19,831
Call me if you need any help.

506
00:33:20,790 --> 00:33:25,086
The conversation we had tonight
has already helped me alot.

507
00:33:27,088 --> 00:33:30,008
I'm feeling a lot better now.

508
00:33:31,926 --> 00:33:34,846
Keeping it bottled inside
ate away at me, you see.

509
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:36,389
Does Ms. Sa know?

510
00:33:37,598 --> 00:33:40,852
I told her and Ms. Lee a few days ago.

511
00:33:42,061 --> 00:33:44,564
-What did they say?
-That's a story for another time.

512
00:33:44,647 --> 00:33:48,860
HE SHOULDN'T KNOW ABOUT
MS. SA'S DIVORCE UNTIL MUCH LATER

513
00:33:49,819 --> 00:33:52,613
You should head back then.
Thank you for today.

514
00:33:53,322 --> 00:33:54,657
I didn't want to go home
to an empty house.

515
00:33:54,741 --> 00:33:58,202
I hate it too,
but it's not so bad sometimes.

516
00:33:58,286 --> 00:33:59,287
When?

517
00:33:59,370 --> 00:34:01,914
After exhausting social gatherings.

518
00:34:01,998 --> 00:34:05,126
They wear you down
and it's tiring to listen to others.

519
00:34:05,626 --> 00:34:08,671
-I'd rather just head home.
-Maybe that's how you feel about today.

