00:50:16,054 --> 00:50:19,808
Bada, who do you take after?

775
00:50:19,891 --> 00:50:21,727
Your mom or your dad?

776
00:50:23,770 --> 00:50:26,106
Aren't you happy to hear my voice again?

777
00:50:30,986 --> 00:50:32,779
Wait, did it just kick?

778
00:50:33,405 --> 00:50:35,532
It answered you and said that it's happy.

779
00:50:40,287 --> 00:50:44,416
For the first time in a while,
I head to the gym

780
00:50:44,499 --> 00:50:47,794
Boy, do I look fine on the treadmill

781
00:50:47,878 --> 00:50:49,921
I run like there's no tomorrow

782
00:50:50,005 --> 00:50:51,715
And that's when I spotted you

783
00:50:51,798 --> 00:50:55,051
You in the short shorts

784
00:50:55,802 --> 00:50:59,514
Your long straight hair is tied back
Your lips are tightly pressed together

785
00:50:59,598 --> 00:51:01,224
Whenever you lift the weights

786
00:51:01,308 --> 00:51:03,435
I'm touched with your grace

787
00:51:03,518 --> 00:51:06,563
Humming to a song
coming from your earphones

788
00:51:08,273 --> 00:51:09,232
Sir.

789
00:51:10,442 --> 00:51:13,737
Could I hold a press conference tomorrow?

790
00:51:15,947 --> 00:51:18,200
Get me some coffee.
One for the makeup artist too.

791
00:51:18,992 --> 00:51:19,993
Sure.

792
00:51:21,578 --> 00:51:22,996
Hello.

793
00:51:25,665 --> 00:51:28,543
I want a natural look today.

794
00:51:32,714 --> 00:51:34,299
BOO HYE-RYUNG PRESS CONFERENCE

795
00:51:36,718 --> 00:51:38,470
Hi there.

796
00:51:41,139 --> 00:51:43,975
-Do you like gatkimchi?
-Of course.

797
00:51:46,686 --> 00:51:48,772
There's juice and also club soda.

798
00:51:48,855 --> 00:51:49,981
No, I'm good.

799
00:51:54,945 --> 00:51:57,072
He has an errand to run.

800
00:51:59,699 --> 00:52:03,370
Side dishes are a nuisance to make.
You didn't need to make this much.

801
00:52:03,453 --> 00:52:06,957
As if this is a lot. It's only the basics.

802
00:52:07,040 --> 00:52:08,708
I have help anyway.

803
00:52:09,709 --> 00:52:12,128
I'll help too once I'm done recovering.

804
00:52:12,212 --> 00:52:13,922
I should learn your recipes.

805
00:52:18,718 --> 00:52:22,222
There's no need to help,
so visit often with the baby.

806
00:52:23,056 --> 00:52:25,267
When will you and Father
come to stay with us?

807
00:52:25,350 --> 00:52:28,436
You two enjoy your time together first.
We're in no rush.

808
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:31,815
It'll be even better with you two.
Double the joy.

809
00:52:37,487 --> 00:52:39,739
Gosh, that looks delicious.

810
00:52:39,823 --> 00:52:41,741
I want to have that for lunch today.

811
00:52:41,825 --> 00:52:43,368
Sure. It'll cleanse your palate.

812
00:52:43,451 --> 00:52:46,788
My bride, you're a bonafide
a Chungcheong-native now.

813
00:52:46,872 --> 00:52:48,832
How can you call me
your bride at this age?

814
00:52:48,915 --> 00:52:50,000
As if you're any old.

815
00:52:50,083 --> 00:52:53,461
In my eyes,
you're still my young, beautiful bride.

816
00:52:54,045 --> 00:52:55,881
She'll say you're being silly.

817
00:52:58,717 --> 00:53:00,760
He's not wrong though.

818
00:53:00,844 --> 00:53:02,929
Not many women are as fair as you.

819
00:53:03,013 --> 00:53:04,472
-Right?
-Of course.

820
00:53:05,265 --> 00:53:07,475
Was it her beauty that you fell for?

821
00:53:07,559 --> 00:53:08,685
Like you have to ask.

822
00:53:11,146 --> 00:53:17,277
BOO HYE-RYUNG PRESS CONFERENCE

823
00:53:19,738 --> 00:53:22,073
BOO HYE-RYUNG

824
00:53:22,157 --> 00:53:25,577
Hello, I see some
familiar faces here today.

825
00:53:25,660 --> 00:53:27,704
Anyway, it saddens me

826
00:53:28,204 --> 00:53:32,000
to deliver the news
that isn't all that pleasant.

827
00:53:34,294 --> 00:53:37,339
I got a divorce.

828
00:53:44,888 --> 00:53:47,307
-When?
-Fairly recently.

829
00:53:47,390 --> 00:53:49,809
Why?
Is it because you have nothing in common?

830
00:53:50,685 --> 00:53:52,979
Is there perhaps another reason?

831
00:53:53,063 --> 00:53:56,524
My husband requested
a divorce and I agreed.

832
00:53:58,526 --> 00:53:59,527
STAR DJ BOO HYE-RYUNG ANNOUNCES DIVORCE

833
00:54:02,447 --> 00:54:04,240
Your husband requested the divorce?

834
00:54:05,241 --> 00:54:06,493
-Yes.
-For what reason?

835
00:54:09,245 --> 00:54:11,915
He met someone new.

836
00:54:11,998 --> 00:54:13,458
So he had an affair?

837
00:54:16,503 --> 00:54:18,380
-Who's the other woman?
-It'sâ¦

838
00:54:19,965 --> 00:54:22,759
not my place to disclose that.

839
00:54:22,842 --> 00:54:24,844
You were married for three years, right?

840
00:54:24,928 --> 00:54:26,096
Yes.

841
00:54:26,179 --> 00:54:28,848
I know this is hard,
but please tell us how you're feeling.

842
00:54:40,026 --> 00:54:42,070
It's just like you said.

843
00:54:42,779 --> 00:54:45,907
Honestly speaking, it's been hard for me.

844
00:54:49,244 --> 00:54:51,371
So you calmly agreed
to the divorce request.

845
00:54:52,956 --> 00:54:54,457
I had no other option.

846
00:54:54,541 --> 00:54:55,959
You could have held out.

847
00:54:57,127 --> 00:54:59,796
How could I when he loves her?

848
00:55:06,511 --> 00:55:07,637
Look after her.

849
00:55:09,264 --> 00:55:12,851
I'm sorry for asking,
but what about the alimony?

850
00:55:12,934 --> 00:55:17,230
I just took what they offered.

851
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:25,530
Your husband is known
to be younger than you.

852
00:55:26,322 --> 00:55:28,408
-By a year.
-How old is the other woman?

853
00:55:28,992 --> 00:55:31,202
-That I don't know--
-Aren't you being too nice?

854
00:55:31,953 --> 00:55:36,166
As a woman myself,
I'd like to keep her privacy.

855
00:55:36,249 --> 00:55:40,295
But she's the woman who stole
your husband. Must you be considerate?

856
00:55:44,132 --> 00:55:47,385
She's pregnant, you see.

857
00:55:54,642 --> 00:55:55,810
BOO HYE-RYUNG'S SHOCKING DIVORCE

858
00:56:04,903 --> 00:56:06,112
No way.

859
00:56:07,072 --> 00:56:08,448
Hye-ryung's divorce was announced.

860
00:56:16,247 --> 00:56:17,707
Were you aware of it?

861
00:56:19,042 --> 00:56:20,585
It's just like you said.

862
00:56:21,252 --> 00:56:23,880
Honestly speaking, it's been hard for me.

863
00:56:27,926 --> 00:56:31,054
BOO HYE-RYUNG ANNOUNCES
THE END OF HER MARRIAGE OF 3 YEARS

864
00:56:40,355 --> 00:56:42,732
What's the deal? Did you get a divorce?

865
00:56:45,235 --> 00:56:46,319
Yes.

866
00:56:47,362 --> 00:56:49,114
Who did you hear that from?

867
00:56:49,197 --> 00:56:51,491
It's a trending topic online right now.

868
00:56:53,493 --> 00:56:55,870
LAW FIRM JIDAM

869
00:57:01,793 --> 00:57:03,294
BOO HYE-RYUNG'S HUSBAND DOXED

870
00:57:14,139 --> 00:57:17,851
Sa-hyeon wants you
to come up with a name for the baby.

871
00:57:17,934 --> 00:57:19,018
Gosh.

872
00:57:19,769 --> 00:57:21,855
Can't we just decide on a random name?

873
00:57:23,022 --> 00:57:26,651
He went to a monk who's good at
creating names for Byeol-hui and Hae-ri.

874
00:57:26,734 --> 00:57:29,195
They're beautiful
and have a great meaning.

875
00:57:29,946 --> 00:57:31,322
They should sound nice too.

876
00:57:31,406 --> 00:57:34,409
Sa-hyeon was given his name
so that he'd be a judge or prosecutor.

877
00:57:35,160 --> 00:57:36,494
"Pan Sa-hyeon."

878
00:57:36,578 --> 00:57:39,706
Better a lawyer
than a judge who punishes people.

879
00:57:40,623 --> 00:57:42,417
My goodness!

880
00:57:43,877 --> 00:57:46,421
Must they ring like that
and startle us silly?

881
00:57:46,504 --> 00:57:49,299
Stay seated.
You shouldn't be getting up like that.

882
00:57:49,382 --> 00:57:50,967
It's all right.

883
00:57:56,806 --> 00:57:59,017
Hi, Yun-sim. It's been a while.

884
00:57:59,100 --> 00:58:02,520
What's the matter with you?
How could you do such a thing?

885
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:05,523
What do you mean?

886
00:58:05,607 --> 00:58:08,234
Your son had an affair
and kicked Boo Hye-ryung out.

887
00:58:10,069 --> 00:58:11,779
That's inhumane, you know.

888
00:58:11,863 --> 00:58:14,616
It's cruel to hurt
other people's children.

889
00:58:14,699 --> 00:58:15,575
Yes?

890
00:58:18,453 --> 00:58:19,370
Where?

891
00:58:20,872 --> 00:58:23,541
-What?
-You have it all wrong.

892
00:58:25,543 --> 00:58:26,669
So?

893
00:58:28,004 --> 00:58:29,380
It's not true.

894
00:58:39,182 --> 00:58:42,018
If my daughter had been
kicked out like Boo Hye-ryung,

895
00:58:42,101 --> 00:58:44,604
I would have buried my son-in-law myself.

896
00:58:44,687 --> 00:58:47,732
No one kicked her out.
She offered to divorce--

897
00:58:47,815 --> 00:58:49,651
Why would she lie about that?

898
00:58:50,235 --> 00:58:51,986
I feel so bad for her.

899
00:58:52,070 --> 00:58:54,280
Even I cried while watching her interview.

900
00:58:54,364 --> 00:58:56,658
You should listen
to both sides of the story.

901
00:58:58,785 --> 00:59:00,119
What you don't know--

902
00:59:04,207 --> 00:59:05,500
I'm getting another call.

903
00:59:14,008 --> 00:59:17,262
Did you read the articles?
Hye-ryung is in no shape to go on air.

904
00:59:17,345 --> 00:59:18,763
We'll have to air a recording.

905
00:59:25,979 --> 00:59:28,815
She seemed okay with it despite the tears.

906
00:59:33,278 --> 00:59:37,031
Wouldn't it have been better
to wait for them to find out?

907
00:59:37,115 --> 00:59:40,159
That's like living
with a ticking time bomb.

908
00:59:41,536 --> 00:59:43,204
It's better to rip off the Band-aid.

909
00:59:43,288 --> 00:59:45,164
They say you can't truly know a person.

910
00:59:47,375 --> 00:59:48,751
Her husband, I mean.

911
00:59:48,835 --> 00:59:51,838
I guess men are defenseless
when women throw themselves at them.

912
00:59:51,921 --> 00:59:55,883
It would have been much better
to not have let it affect him though.

913
00:59:55,967 --> 00:59:57,176
The gossip will subside.

914
00:59:57,260 --> 01:00:01,139
That will be true for Ms. Boo
and she'll win sympathy votes too.

915
01:00:02,515 --> 01:00:04,726
But her husband
is being dragged through the mud.

916
01:00:04,809 --> 01:00:07,353
What can you do? He had it coming.

917
01:00:08,771 --> 01:00:11,733
You're saying that
because you're also a man, right?

918
01:00:11,816 --> 01:00:13,151
Because all guys stick together?

919
01:00:13,234 --> 01:00:14,986
-Is that not true?
-Of course not.

920
01:00:15,570 --> 01:00:17,405
He was once her husband,

921
01:00:17,488 --> 01:00:19,657
so did she have to bury him socially?

922
01:00:20,325 --> 01:00:22,243
People who don't know him will forget

923
01:00:22,327 --> 01:00:25,204
and move on to new gossip,

924
01:00:25,288 --> 01:00:27,040
but not those close to him.

925
01:00:27,123 --> 01:00:28,625
It'll be hard on his parents too.

926
01:00:28,708 --> 01:00:30,627
I guess she didn't see it coming.

927
01:00:30,710 --> 01:00:33,796
She was only trying to take initiative
before word got out.

928
01:00:34,839 --> 01:00:37,884
You know how manic people get
over other people's lives.

929
01:00:39,510 --> 01:00:41,763
There was no need to dox her husband.

930
01:00:41,846 --> 01:00:46,225
Could news about Hae-ryun's engagement
to Nam Ga-bin hurt our kids?

931
01:00:47,810 --> 01:00:50,897
The wrong person
can ruin a whole household,

932
01:00:51,564 --> 01:00:53,191
and that's exactly what happened.

933
01:00:54,192 --> 01:00:56,903
How could she stab us
in the back like this?

934
01:00:56,986 --> 01:00:58,738
Unbelievable.

935
01:00:59,530 --> 01:01:01,866
No wonder they say humans are the worst.

936
01:01:03,701 --> 01:01:07,330
You're a poor judge of character.
And you call yourself a lawyer?

937
01:01:07,413 --> 01:01:09,874
You just fell for her pretty face.

938
01:01:10,458 --> 01:01:12,835
That can be said for us too.

939
01:01:12,919 --> 01:01:14,796
I was clearly against the marriage.

940
01:01:14,879 --> 01:01:17,006
-I'm sorry.
-What did your boss say?

941
01:01:17,090 --> 01:01:18,508
Didn't he tell you to resign

942
01:01:19,634 --> 01:01:21,803
for tarnishing the firm's reputation?

943
01:01:22,303 --> 01:01:25,139
There's no loyalty
among colleagues when in a crisis.

944
01:01:25,223 --> 01:01:26,766
Let's just give it a few days.

945
01:01:26,849 --> 01:01:29,227
How could she when we did
everything she asked for?

946
01:01:29,310 --> 01:01:31,479
She even bought dinner to thank us.

947
01:01:32,146 --> 01:01:34,315
She even mentioned Catholicism

948
01:01:34,399 --> 01:01:37,694
and said she'll just
accept things as they are.

949
01:01:37,777 --> 01:01:42,031
She also said she'd see us
as her parents and not her in-laws.

950
01:01:42,115 --> 01:01:44,367
She even said she'd visit us in Daejeon.

951
01:01:45,702 --> 01:01:47,453
And with a smile on her face!

952
01:01:47,537 --> 01:01:50,415
It hasn't even been a month.
It was two days ago!

953
01:01:51,416 --> 01:01:55,253
Divorce isn't anything to be proud of,
so why hold a press conference?

954
01:01:55,336 --> 01:01:57,839
I get why she announced it,

955
01:01:57,922 --> 01:01:59,507
but how could she

956
01:01:59,590 --> 01:02:02,635
make Sa-hyeon look like
the vilest cheater on Earth?

957
01:02:02,719 --> 01:02:05,304
We even hugged when we parted ways

958
01:02:06,431 --> 01:02:08,599
-and wished each other the best.
-Why would you?

959
01:02:09,142 --> 01:02:10,977
It was a way of saying goodbye.

960
01:02:11,060 --> 01:02:13,730
You see foreigners do it in movies.

961
01:02:13,813 --> 01:02:15,022
And this is what she does?

962
01:02:15,106 --> 01:02:16,899
Just how many faces does she have?

963
01:02:16,983 --> 01:02:19,986
I shouldn't have told her
to visit us when she golfed.

964
01:02:22,363 --> 01:02:24,407
She played us.

965
01:02:24,490 --> 01:02:28,327
After taking what she needed from us,
she told her story in tears.

966
01:02:28,411 --> 01:02:30,705
Why not say he crippled her heart too?

967
01:02:31,539 --> 01:02:34,083
Could it be that she never had one
in the first place?

968
01:02:34,167 --> 01:02:35,501
Just think about it.

969
01:02:35,585 --> 01:02:38,671
How could she do something like this?

970
01:02:39,172 --> 01:02:42,633
She may be pretty on the outside,
but how ugly can she be on the inside?

971
01:02:42,717 --> 01:02:44,552
I can't show my face anymore.

972
01:02:44,635 --> 01:02:47,096
Everyone I know
wants nothing to do with me now.

973
01:02:47,180 --> 01:02:48,598
What about him then?

974
01:02:48,681 --> 01:02:51,309
No firm in Korea
will want to work with him now.

975
01:02:51,392 --> 01:02:53,269
He's still young!

976
01:02:54,729 --> 01:02:56,773
I'm sorry. This is all my fault.

977
01:02:58,608 --> 01:03:00,860
How is this your fault? It isn't.

978
01:03:00,943 --> 01:03:03,863
-Of course not.
-The marriage was cursed, to begin with.

979
01:03:04,447 --> 01:03:06,365
There's even a song about it.

980
01:03:07,158 --> 01:03:09,076
-Right?
-Yes.

981
01:03:11,120 --> 01:03:12,997
You and your poor judge of people.

982
01:03:13,080 --> 01:03:16,667
You should have checked to see
if she was pretty on the inside too.

983
01:03:16,751 --> 01:03:17,835
Just like your mom.

984
01:03:18,419 --> 01:03:20,463
Don't stress yourself over this.

985
01:03:20,546 --> 01:03:22,924
-This is our issue to handle.
-Of course.

986
01:03:25,343 --> 01:03:26,803
Meet your future sister-in-law.

987
01:03:28,471 --> 01:03:31,808
It's nice to see you again
as a future family member.

988
01:03:31,891 --> 01:03:32,975
Same here.

989
01:03:45,613 --> 01:03:47,365
I'll be back in just a moment.

990
01:03:54,997 --> 01:03:58,209
What's done is done,
so as long as we pull it together--

991
01:03:59,961 --> 01:04:01,170
You should turn it off.

992
01:04:04,841 --> 01:04:06,133
It's Hye-ryung.

993
01:04:06,926 --> 01:04:08,302
Answer it.

994
01:04:12,431 --> 01:04:16,018
-Yes?
-Father, I'm terribly sorry.

995
01:04:16,686 --> 01:04:19,313
The reporters spun my story their own way.

996
01:04:19,397 --> 01:04:21,315
-Is that so?
-Yes.

997
01:04:22,358 --> 01:04:26,863
Those reportersâ¦ Their only concern
is to sensationalize the story.

998
01:04:27,822 --> 01:04:29,156
I regret doing the interview.

999
01:04:29,240 --> 01:04:30,491
Weren't you the one who said it?

1000
01:04:30,575 --> 01:04:33,661
As you know, what we say
can be taken in the wrong way.

1001
01:04:33,744 --> 01:04:35,663
You parted ways with a smile on your face,

1002
01:04:36,372 --> 01:04:37,665
but there you were in tears.

1003
01:04:37,748 --> 01:04:40,042
The reporters hounded me with questions

1004
01:04:40,126 --> 01:04:42,795
and that led to a burst of emotions.

1005
01:04:44,088 --> 01:04:45,965
I couldn't lie

1006
01:04:46,048 --> 01:04:49,343
and the truth would come out anyway
even if I tried to keep it a secret.

1007
01:04:50,219 --> 01:04:52,179
Things might have backfired.

1008
01:04:53,681 --> 01:04:56,976
I only stuck to the facts,
but that's how they wrote their articles.

1009
01:04:57,685 --> 01:04:59,228
I feel terrible myself.

1010
01:04:59,812 --> 01:05:02,648
-About what?
-I've made a big mess of things.

1011
01:05:02,732 --> 01:05:05,359
They were going to find out anyway,

1012
01:05:05,443 --> 01:05:07,320
so I wanted to break the news myself.

1013
01:05:08,070 --> 01:05:10,072
It's always better
to rip the Band-aid off.

1014
01:05:10,156 --> 01:05:12,241
There was no Band-aid on your arm though.

1015
01:05:12,742 --> 01:05:13,951
Only on ours.

1016
01:05:14,035 --> 01:05:17,204
The biggest one was on Sa-hyeon.

1017
01:05:17,288 --> 01:05:19,290
The whole nation calls him a bastard now.

1018
01:05:19,373 --> 01:05:20,458
Is it that bad?

1019
01:05:20,541 --> 01:05:23,878
He was doxed thanks to you.
Didn't you know?

1020
01:05:23,961 --> 01:05:27,298
I was too upset
to read any of the articles.

1021
01:05:27,381 --> 01:05:28,257
Is that so?

1022
01:05:28,341 --> 01:05:31,177
Anyway, it'll soon blow over.

1023
01:05:31,802 --> 01:05:34,388
-Don't worry too much.
-Is that why you called?

1024
01:05:34,472 --> 01:05:36,182
-Yes.
-All right then.

1025
01:05:36,265 --> 01:05:39,310
Sure thing. Have a good day, Father.

1026
01:05:48,277 --> 01:05:50,029
That conniving snake.

1027
01:05:50,112 --> 01:05:51,447
What did she say?

1028
01:05:51,530 --> 01:05:53,783
Mom, what are you up to?

1029
01:05:55,660 --> 01:05:58,162
I know. Things were tense today.

1030
01:05:59,914 --> 01:06:01,999
Don't you worry.

1031
01:06:02,083 --> 01:06:05,002
I actually have a better image now
because of it.

1032
01:06:05,628 --> 01:06:07,421
The sympathy votes keep coming in.

1033
01:06:10,716 --> 01:06:13,052
Won't you and Dad visit sometime?

1034
01:06:13,552 --> 01:06:16,013
My new house is wonderful.

1035
01:06:16,931 --> 01:06:19,642
The view of the Han River at night
is amazing.

1036
01:06:36,492 --> 01:06:39,495
Goodness. Are you here by yourself?

1037
01:06:39,578 --> 01:06:40,997
Yes.

1038
01:06:42,331 --> 01:06:44,417
-Really?
-Have I ever lied to you?

1039
01:06:44,500 --> 01:06:47,920
That's not what I was implying.
Maybe a joke perhaps.

1040
01:06:49,964 --> 01:06:52,675
Did you go that day
to see your friend Madam Hong?

1041
01:06:52,758 --> 01:06:55,845
-No, so my friends came by my house.
-Do you invite people over?

1042
01:06:57,221 --> 01:06:59,015
You seem to enjoy being alone.

1043
01:07:00,683 --> 01:07:02,476
I get that Ms. Boo can't be here,

1044
01:07:03,769 --> 01:07:05,312
but I'm sure Ms. Lee came.

1045
01:07:07,523 --> 01:07:08,691
She went to the restroom.

1046
01:07:20,036 --> 01:07:21,996
It'll be past ten when it's over.

1047
01:07:30,171 --> 01:07:31,839
Is Ms. Lee still not back?

1048
01:07:34,050 --> 01:07:35,676
Maybe she isn't feeling well.

1049
01:07:37,386 --> 01:07:38,888
Will you get her some medicine too?

1050
01:07:40,556 --> 01:07:41,432
I came alone.

1051
01:07:42,558 --> 01:07:44,393
Did she already see this show?

1052
01:07:44,477 --> 01:07:46,270
You should ask her later.

1053
01:07:47,396 --> 01:07:48,564
Thanks for this.

1054
01:07:50,858 --> 01:07:52,610
Do you like this musical?

1055
01:07:53,319 --> 01:07:54,695
Are you a fan of Nam Ga-bin's?

1056
01:07:55,696 --> 01:07:57,198
I just thought I should watch it.

1057
01:08:00,618 --> 01:08:03,579
I feel bad. I shouldn't have
joked about her being here.

1058
01:08:04,538 --> 01:08:08,084
Food shouldn't be wasted,
and also beverages for that matter.

1059
01:08:08,167 --> 01:08:09,710
Of course not.

1060
01:08:10,377 --> 01:08:12,213
How can you drink two cups though?

1061
01:08:29,772 --> 01:08:30,689
Goodness.

1062
01:08:37,279 --> 01:08:38,781
Isn't that your husband?

1063
01:08:41,242 --> 01:08:42,451
It is.

1064
01:09:31,709 --> 01:09:33,210
You better shut your trap

1065
01:09:33,294 --> 01:09:34,420
before I pour cold soup over you.

1066
01:09:34,503 --> 01:09:35,754
They're my eyes.
I'll do what I like with them.

1067
01:09:35,838 --> 01:09:37,882
-Why youâ¦
-You're going to pour cold soup over me?

1068
01:09:42,678 --> 01:09:45,431
It's been so long since I last
saw you laugh out loud like this.

1069
01:09:45,514 --> 01:09:48,184
I'll be honest.
I have a thing for Mr. Seo.

1070
01:09:48,267 --> 01:09:49,643
You will help me, right?

1071
01:09:49,727 --> 01:09:51,520
So you're going to beat me to it?

1072
01:09:51,604 --> 01:09:55,191
She's nuts. How could she
put her hands on the elderly?

1073
01:09:55,274 --> 01:09:56,483
Why do you always have to fight?

1074
01:09:56,567 --> 01:09:58,694
I'm truly grateful
for what you did for me.

1075
01:09:58,777 --> 01:10:03,782
I'm over what we went through in the past,
so you don't have to feel sorry.

1076
01:10:05,034 --> 01:10:06,076
Let's get married.

1077
01:10:06,160 --> 01:10:09,580
She's seeing that Mr. Seo guy.
I don't know since when though.

1078
01:10:09,663 --> 01:10:11,707
You've played me for a fool.

1079
01:10:11,790 --> 01:10:13,292
And yet you blamed me for everything.

1080
01:10:13,375 --> 01:10:15,669
-That's ridiculous.
-I'll take care of Ji-a from now on.

1081
01:10:16,712 --> 01:10:21,133
